The '''Ministry of Communications and Information Technology''' ({{lang-my|ဆက်သွယ်ရေးနှင့် သတင်းအချက်အလက် နည်းပညာဝန်ကြီးဌာန}}; abbreviated ''' MCIT''') administers Myanmar's communications and [[information technology]] policies. The ministry was formerly known as the '''Ministry of Communications, Posts and Telegraphs'''.
The Ministry was organized as '''Ministry of Transport and Communication''' by Htin Kyaw's Cabinet in 2016.
